reviews.text: A Chiu Chow style cuisine restaurant. Ordered a dinner set for four to serve among friends of three. Chose this restaurant because of its location and close proximity to Jordan MTR Station. The restaurant wasn't crowded even during dinner peak hour. Relatively relaxing for friends gathering. The food quality was just OK. Prices not too high. We liked the soup and noodles. Other dishes barely met expectations.

the fish was the best~ 
but the food was salty in general (except the tasteless jellyfish)
prices are reasonable on some dishes while overpriced on some others.....
all-in-all, i won’t consider this place for Chiu Chow food (given I grow up in a Chiu Chow family)
It's fine if not too high expectations
Nice food with reasonable price

reviews.text: Local dim sum in k- town which opens at 2am and closes at 4pm. Pretty much all the time packed full.  Food is very nice.. nevertheless a real local experience to eat there... don't expect any English speaking staff

Good dim sum. It's chaotic when it's busy but this is where locals eat. Go there for the experience. The price about the same as other places. It was really busy at 8:30am and even busier at noon the two times I went. The service is fast and tables are shared. You do have to go up to a counter to get your own dishes but sometimes they come by with some straight from the kitchen to offer you.

Take out is also available and advisable if there's a line up. It's a small place so they can't seat many but they do cram in a lot into a tiny place.

Very authentic dim sum dishes. Price is very affordable while quality is at par with up class restaurants. However it is a very local establishment with no decoration and simple set up. It opens at 0300in the morning.  Most of the time customers had to que up for entrance . Best time visit-very early in the morning before0730, it closes after 1600 .

They close at 4 and I went at around 3.30. The lady was rushing me to choose food that was already cooked. The steamed beef rice rolls were a bit old honestly I couldn't finish that. But other than that, other items were good. And i managed to order a freshly steamed prawn dumplings, those were great. So my suggestion is go early!!
It's worth coming here once for the experience. It's usually packed with locals and noisy. There isn't much space among the tables. The food is acceptable and cheap.

reviews.text: 流沙包好吃💓
好食👍👍👍
아침 7시에도 사람들이 많네요..대부분 현지 어르신들..먹고 죽을 정도로 맛난것은 아닙니다. 가성비 좋구 현지 느낌 같이 느끼는게 더 좋은 곳인거 같습니다. 굉장히 다양한 종류를 즉석에서 눈으로 골라먹는 재미 추천.. 아주 친절하지는 않지만 그리 불친절하지도 않습니다. 영어가 안됩니다. 바디랭귀지로 해결하셔야 됩니다. 깔끔한걸 원하시는 분들께는 비추.

新興食家位於堅尼地城站步行約5分鐘便可到達。
營業時間都非常特別，自凌晨3點開門營直至下午4點，晚上訓唔著，真係可以3點就落離飲個茶都得。

店內擺放了約九、十張桌子，坐起來位置比較擠迫，如果人數不足以坐一整桌，需要併桌而坐。

而且地板與桌子通常不算太乾淨，大家出入都要小心地滑！

為求食品日日新鮮點心售完即止，價錢實惠，性價比高，怪不得客似雲來。

廚房是半開放式，環境乾淨，還可看到點心師傅忙碌地制作點心。

在這裡享用點心都需要眼明手快，因為每次有點心出爐，店員都會大叫xx點心，然後問食客要不要？如果手慢，就有機會要等下一輪啦，因為你想食既野已經比人拎哂啦。

而另一邊都擺放著點心，但當然唔及廚房個邊，剛剛出爐咁熱咁新鮮啦。

皇牌流沙包 - $21
把流沙包一分為二時，小心燙手(口)，香滑的奶皇餡就這樣流了出來，奶皇餡香氣撲鼻。奶皇餡幼滑細緻，感覺得到一粒粒的蛋黃細沙，而且甜味當中，亦帶鹹香，令人非常滿足。

咖哩金錢肚 - $20
金錢肚切得又大又厚，卻相當入味，食落牛肚鮮甜有口感，還有濃郁的咖裡的香味。

豉汁蒸鳳爪 - $20
豉汁蒸鳳爪色澤光澤，汁濃而帶點辣，惹味非常。
